And they do not contain any mercury.
Several specialists pointed out that compact phosphor pears exhibit reserves, since them mercury to contain and that one must dispose of it therefore as special refuse, which is not always possible in the developing countries except the producers makes available an assumption place.
The main source at mercury emissions on the planet does not represent the compact phosphor pear according to the report however, but rather the coal-fired power stations, which discharge substantially more mercury, in order to produce the electricity wasted by the white-hot pears.
However in the United States these coal-fired power stations discharge 25.000 tons mercury annually.
